  "text": "The Prometheus Alertmanager notification pipeline traces the flow of alerts from ingestion through routing, filtering, and final dispatch to notification receivers. Here are the key components:\n\n1. **Alert Ingestion**: The pipeline begins in cmd/alertmanager/main.go which sets up the alertmanager service. Alerts are ingested through the Dispatcher (dispatch/dispatch.go:89), created via NewDispatcher() (dispatch/dispatch.go:132). The Dispatcher.Run() method (dispatch/dispatch.go:170) starts multiple alert ingestion workers that subscribe to alerts via provider.Alerts.SlurpAndSubscribe(). Incoming alerts are processed through Dispatcher.routeAlert() (dispatch/dispatch.go:274).\n\n2. **Routing Tree Traversal**: The routing decision happens in Route.Match() (dispatch/route.go:160), which performs a depth-first left-to-right search through the routing tree. The Route struct (dispatch/route.go:42) and NewRoute() (dispatch/route.go:63) build the hierarchical routing configuration. Each alert is matched against the route tree to determine which receivers should handle it.\n\n3. **Alert Grouping**: After routing, alerts are grouped in Dispatcher.groupAlert() (dispatch/dispatch.go:443), which creates aggregation groups based on the matched route and grouped labels. The aggrGroup struct (dispatch/dispatch.go:605) represents a group of alerts with common routing options. These groups are started by Dispatcher.runAG() (dispatch/dispatch.go:570).\n\n4. **Inhibition Check**: Within the notification pipeline stages, the MuteStage (notify/mute.go:47) applies inhibition rules. It uses the Inhibitor interface (inhibit/inhibit.go:42) created via NewInhibitor() (inhibit/inhibit.go:54). The key check happens in Inhibitor.Mutes() (inhibit/inhibit.go:183), which evaluates InhibitRules (inhibit/inhibit.go:226) to determine if an alert should be suppressed because a higher-level alert with matching labels is firing.\n\n5. **Silence Check**: Also within the MuteStage, silence filtering is applied through the Silencer interface (silence/silence.go:145), created via NewSilencer(). The Silencer.Mutes() method (silence/silence.go:163) queries the Silences store (silence/silence.go) to check if an alert matches any active or pending silences, using both cache-based fast paths and full silence matching.\n\n6. **Notifier Dispatch**: The final dispatch stage is orchestrated by PipelineBuilder (notify/notify.go:421) and its New() method (notify/notify.go:434), which constructs a multi-stage pipeline. The pipeline includes GossipSettleStage (cluster coordination), MuteStage (inhibition and silence filtering), TimeActiveStage/TimeMuteStage (time-based routing), and per-receiver notification stages using Integration.Notify() (notify/notify.go:90). Each stage implements the Stage interface (notify/notify.go:286), and stages are executed sequentially as the alerts flow through the pipeline via aggrGroup.run() (dispatch/dispatch.go:667).\n\nThe complete flow: main -> Dispatcher.Run -> routeAlert -> Route.Match -> groupAlert -> aggrGroup.run -> PipelineBuilder stages (including Inhibitor.Mutes and Silencer.Mutes) -> Integration.Notify."
}

